            <title>[SOLR-7206] MiniSolrCloudCluster needs to check for SSL config when starting up</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7206</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Just tripped this on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4044&quot; title=&quot;CloudSolrServer early connect problems&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4044&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4044&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  If you start MiniSolrCloudCluster up with SSL enabled in its JettyConfig, the cloud client won&apos;t work because it will try and communicate via http, rather than https.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
